      "content": "friends and doctors dont really get it. they just tell me to 'manage' it or 'cope'. but how do you cope with something that's just... permanent? it feels less like a battle and more like a slow sinking. sometimes i look at it and just think, wouldn't it be such a mercy if it all just stopped? just total stillness.",
